      <h4>YOU GOT QUESTIONS, WE GOT ANSWERS</h4>
      <br>
      <h5 class="logo-color">What do you mean by "stuff"? What will I be able to borrow or lend?</h5>
      <p>Currently, we have mostly camping/ backpacking gear, tools, housewares, and kitchen appliances <b><i>(play around with the pictures at right to check out stuff that our early users have borrowed!)</i></b>. When borrowers request something we don't have, that's when we start to ask lenders if they have this item. This way, we ensure that we have stuff that people want.</p>

      <h5 class="logo-color">What happens if a lender's stuff is damaged or lost?</h5>
      <p>Borrowers are getting stuff from friends or friends-of-friends, so damages or losses rarely happen. But we have clear <%= link_to 'Terms of Service', terms_path, { style: "color:#428bca", target: "_blank" } %> that outlines exactly how these situations will be resolved. We'll do whatever we can to ensure everyone has a great experience sharing.</p>

      <h5 class="logo-color">Why do I need Project Borrow? Can't I just call friends?</h5>
      <p>We've found it's hard to borrow stuff outside a circle of 2-3 close friends because you don't want to feel like you're always asking for favors. On the other hand, most lenders actually don't give this a second thought! Therefore, Project Borrow aims to take all awkwardness out, add in some security, and make sharing fun & easy for everyone!</p>

      <h5 class="logo-color">Does Project Borrow deliver?</h5>
      <p>We offer optional delivery for a fee. In many instances though, we find that it's pretty easy to pick up or return from someone you know.</p>

      <p><i>Have another question? <%= mail_to 'james@projectborrow.com', 'Send us an email', { style: "color:#428bca"}%></i></p>
